-- F&C shareholders vote in favour of BMO takeover
-- By Chris Vellacott
-- Tue Mar 25, 2014 09:00AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, March 25 (Reuters) - Shareholders in F&C Asset Management have voted in favour of a 708 million pounds ($1.17 billion) takeover bid by Canadian lender Bank of Montreal <BMO.TO>.

At a meeting, votes representing 99.6 percent of F&C's shares supported the deal, the fund manager said in a statement on Tuesday. The company added that trading in F&C shares will be suspended after the market close on May 6.